								<div class="title" id="post-title-4136627">
																		New Branch
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/erudius-nacht" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5040209); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5040209&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204538" alt="Erudius Nacht" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5040209)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/erudius-nacht" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5040209); return false;" >Erudius Nacht</a></span> <span class="odate time_1548917219 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">31 Jan 2019 06:46</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4136627">
									

<p>First of all, a big big thanks to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/proasek" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2048131); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2048131&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1555957277" alt="Proasek" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2048131)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/proasek" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2048131); return false;">Proasek</a></span> for his guidance and approval on the new branch. The style is a modified version of <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/ambrose-thorn-valley">Amber Thorn Valley</a> by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mayoculpa" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3489662); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3489662&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1555957277" alt="mayoculpa" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3489662)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mayoculpa" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3489662); return false;">mayoculpa</a></span>. It's an ironed banana leaf version of the Ambrose format.</p>
<p>Now unto the food. As you may have noticed, its all monsters or sacred beasts from local mythology. The way it's served however is reminiscent of Filipino cuisine and culture. Filipinos love buffets, eating in a group, and dishing out a copious amount of it on ironed banana leaves. There is a lot of meat (seafood counts as meat), and the cooking styles can be interchanged with each meat. Filipinos are heavy meat eaters, hardly any vegans, and some of the leading causes of mortality are hypertensive stroke, heart disease, diabetes and colon cancer, and I tried to reflect all of that in the piece.</p>
<p>Some of other elements also come from Filipino Mythology, such as reversing your shirt when lost and Maria Makiling's mountain. The Mountain and University exists in reality, but it's one of the more anomalous tourist spots in the Philippines.</p>
<p>I hope you enjoy it. Thanks. <span style="font-size:50%;">P.S. There's a secret menu.</span></p>
<p>Misty Forest picture is from:<br />
<a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mud_Spring,_Mount_Makiling_-_panoramio.jpg">https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mud_Spring,_Mount_Makiling_-_panoramio.jpg</a></p>
<p>The two <em>Baybayin</em> texts were generated using <a href="https://www.lexilogos.com/keyboard/baybayin.htm">this</a> and made into transparent background images by me.</p>
<div class="image-container alignleft"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/ambrose-makiling/Mabuhay.png" alt="Mabuhay.png" class="image" /></div>
<p>&quot;Mabuhay&quot; - common Tagalog greeting meaning &quot;Live Prosperously&quot;</p>
<img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/ambrose-makiling/Paalam.png" alt="Paalam.png" class="image" /><br />
&quot;Paalam at Salamat&quot; - translated as &quot;Farewell and Thanks&quot;
							</div>

										<div class="signature">
					<hr class="signature-separator"/>
					

<p>Early trust is akin to apathy. Doubt, like all poisons, can be a tonic.</p>

				</div>
					
